{"id": "unknown-2026-04-28-007", "date": "2026-04-28", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Tue"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["weak"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Empyrean draws retail inflows while profit falls, testing China EDA valuations", "content": "China's domestic EDA software developer Empyrean Technology is attracting a growing base of retail investors even as its earnings weaken, underscoring a widening gap between market enthusiasm for semiconductor design tools and near-term profitability.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260428VL212/eda-profit-retail-software-design.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-28-008", "date": "2026-04-28", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Tue"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["earnings"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.75, "reasons": ["涉及財報"]}, "title": "Macronix returns to profit in 1Q26, citing tighter supply and higher memory prices", "content": "Macronix's return to profitability in the first quarter of 2026 signals supply constraints and stronger memory pricing, with implications for global flash markets and customer supply chains. The Taiwan-based memory maker reported wider margins, robust NAND growth, and reduced inventories, suggesting that tighter industry supply and higher ASPs could significantly reshape pricing and sourcing worldwide.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260428PD214/2026-profit-nand-revenue-growth.html", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "lg_elec-2026-04-28-009", "date": "2026-04-28", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Tue"}, "entities": {"companies": ["lg_elec"], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["automotive_display"], "sentiment": {"label": "positive", "score": 0.5, "keywords": ["expand"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "LG reportedly plans to expand its India manufacturing footprint", "content": "<em>New Daily</em> reports that LG Electronics has decided to expand its manufacturing footprint in India, with a major investment of about KRW1.4 trillion (approximately US$1.0 billion) to upgrade its home appliance production facility in Greater Noida. The move comes as LG Group Chair Koo Kwang-mo participates in a presidential economic delegation visiting India and Vietnam, underscoring the strategic importance of the investment timing.", "sources": [{"name": "digitimes_display", "url": "https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20260428VL211/manufacturing-lg-investment-lg-electronics-production.html", "type": "rss"}]}
